      "comment": "Star filly WISHING BELLE (8) makes her return after ending her juvenile season with a string of wins, the last of them coming in September's G1 Westbred Classic. She is four from four at this circuit and distance and also unbeaten fresh. Draws wide but has the class to overcome that. SOVEREIGN JEWEL (4) made a successful return when she led from a similar draw and went on to score by 7 metres at Bunbury last start. Has upside and won her only previous second-up attempt so can progress. MISS LEOPATRA NZ (1) broke her maiden when winning here last start. Up in grade but gets the ace draw and is open to further improvement third up. CHEFS KISS (7) will be fitter after returning from a let-up with a placing from this barrier last start at Bunbury.",
